title: TV show ratings: The Muppets and Agents of SHIELD slide on Tuesday - Agents of SHIELD Cult
text: The Muppets continued its ratings descent on Tuesday (October 13), according to Nielsen figures.The comedy series dipped three-tenths of a point to 1.3 (4.34m) at 8pm on ABC, while Fresh Off the Boat took 1.4 (3.96m) at 8.30pm. © ABC Agents of SHIELD dropped two-tenths at 9pm on ABC with 1.4 (3.74m).Last night's Democratic presidential debate attracted a massive 15.3m viewers on CNN. NBC won the key 18-49 demographic on the major networks on Tuesday with 1.8.Best Time Ever with Neil Patrick Harris started off the night on NBC with 1.2 (4.48m) at 8pm, and The Voice rose to 2.6 (10.14m).Chicago Fire was way down from last fall's 2.6, averaging 1.8 (7.37m) at 10pm on NBC. © The CW / Cate Cameron The Flash largely held its ground with 1.4 (3.49m) at 8pm on The CW, followed by iZombie dropping to 0.5 (1.22m) at 9pm.CBS's NCIS and NCIS: New Orleans grabbed 2.1 (16.04m) at 8pm and 1.5 (12.47m) at 9pm, but Limitless dropped three-tenths to 1.4 (8.03m) at 10pm.Fox's comedy block of Grandfathered and The Grinder reached 1.0 (3.17m) at 8pm and 0.9 (2.53m) at 8.30pm.At 9pm on Fox, Scream Queens dipped again with 1.0 (2.39m).
